**Password** — argon2id (memory-hard, never MD5/SHA); **byte cap applied before normalization/hashing** (DoS guard, also dodges bcrypt's 72-byte pitfall); 12–128 length; 3-of-4 character-class rule; repeated-run and common-sequence rejection; must not contain username/email local-part; **HIBP k-anonymity breach check** (only a 5-char SHA-1 prefix leaves the host, padded responses, fails open on outage).

